<terminology>
    <the_waycast id='the_waycast_defined'>
        The general form of a waycast
          <!-- Changing?  sync'd → http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/cast/waycast  HERE CUSTOM -->
        <waycast>
            A formal declaration of a way and the commitment to act on it
              <!-- A declaration, not a definition; a single waycast is declarative of a way,
                 not necessarily definitive.  The definition may be spread across multiple waycasts
                 via intercast waylinks.  Changing?  sync'd → /README.html, /way.xht,  HERE CUSTOM
                                           http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/cast/waycast  HERE CUSTOM -->
            <_same cog:link='/engineer/wayics/#way_defined'/>
            </waycast>
        </the_waycast>
    </terminology>



<constraint_G id='ever_G'>
    Always the waycast relates the personal to the endmost goal of the person
    <_ cog:link='/philosopher/ethics/moral_form/#G'/>
    </constraint_G>



<constraint_F id='ever_F'>
    Always the waycast promotes a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom
    <_ cog:link='/philosopher/ethics/moral_form/#F'/>
    <_>
        The waycast is personal property, to shape and fill according to one’s will
        </_>
    <_ id='availability'>
        A waycast of one’s own is available to anyone who wants it
        <_>The waycast propagates by free copying</_>
        <_>
            The waycast is a public facility
            </_>
        </_>
    <_>
        The waycast is inalienable from the person
        </_>
    <postulate>
        Personal ownership of used tools increases personal freedom
        </postulate>
    </constraint_F>



